{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASSED at HEAD dec75f22 (run 4; epic 3156 also re-attested + now in_progress). Advisory triage: the 15 residual advisories are plan-text-vs-implementation deltas — the description still describes the earlier module-dict/mtime memo + the abandoned batch.extra_criteria fan-out, but the landed implementation already adopts the BETTER form each advisory asks for: (1) effective_routing/load_criteria are @lru_cache(maxsize=128) keyed by (repo_root, sha256(overlay-bytes)) — content-hash not mtime, bounded eviction not an unbounded dict; (2) prompt_library._invalidate_caches() clears both new lru_caches (test_editing_overlay_invalidates + test asserts); (3) project fan-out is runner-side (ProductionBatchRunner appends the project. subset of route_criteria) since the v3 batch schema is immutable + the gate self-validates — gates/plan-review.yaml + the schema are UNCHANGED; include_project_<name> is the sanitized coverage/routing record. Re-editing the description to chase each advisory would re-invalidate the just-earned attestation (material change) and loop, so captured here instead. registry_version(repo_root) overlay-hashing + attestation invalidation is explicitly story 08af (not this MVP root)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782878872832637001,"uuid":"720d93e7-1ca9-4ca8-8f46-1632013ac0d3"}